Topic: Unsolicited hashtag#SEO tip

summary: This post argues that AI citations alone are not an accurate measure of brand visibility in AI search. Using an example, the author shows that while an AI response repeatedly recommends Audi models, the citation points to another website, making it appear as though Audi has no visibility. The post suggests that brands should evaluate both mentions and citations when measuring AI search performance. The key message is that businesses should focus on whether their brand is recommended, not just whether their website is cited.
Key Takeaways:
Takeaway 1 Citations don't tell the full story
Takeaway 2 Measure brand mentions alongside citations
Takeaway 3 Focus on user impact


