Topic: Search 'n Stuff talk.
Summary: This post introduces a framework for measuring the business impact of AI Search using observed, proxy, and modeled metrics. It explains that organizations should distinguish between directly measurable outcomes, benchmark estimates, and revenue projections to better understand AI Search performance. The featured cheat sheet outlines key metrics such as AI-referred sessions, AI-assisted conversions, AI visibility, and influenced revenue. The goal is to help businesses track AI Search success with realistic, data-driven measurement methods.

Key Takeaways:This post outlines five essential KPIs for measuring a brand's visibility in AI search results. Instead of relying solely on rankings, it recommends tracking prompt coverage, recommendation rate, linked citation rate, comparative win rate, and representation accuracy. These metrics help businesses understand not only whether their brand appears in AI-generated responses, but also how accurately and favorably it is presented. The framework encourages a more comprehensive approach to evaluating AI search performance and brand presence
Takeaway 1 Measure more than visibility
Takeaway 2 Focus on AI-specific KPIs
Takeaway 3 Monitor brand perception in AI
